sentences: John William Stevenson (born September 10, 1963) is an American musician and record producer.
He went on to record with Black Flag on several of their albums until 1985, including the highly influential My War.
After this he focused his attention on Descendents and played with the band until lead singer Milo Aukerman left in 1987.
All went on to have two more singers, Scott Reynolds (1989–1993) and Chad Price (1993–present).

One of Stevenson's most recent works is producing Rise Against's seventh studio album, The Black Market, which was released July 15, 2014, As I Lay Dying's Awakened as well as the 2012 NOFX album Self Entitled.

Bill Stevenson (birth name; John William Stevenson) was born on September 10, 1963.
Stevenson is an original member of the Descendents forming in 1978.
The Descendents put out a single called "Ride the Wild / It's a Hectic World" in 1979.
In 1982 they put out their first album Milo Goes to College.
He left Black Flag in 1985 to reform the Descendents.
The Descendents became All in 1988 after Aukerman left once again.
The Descendents would form again from 1996 to 1997 and then in 2002, before going on hiatus.
The Descendents would form again from 1996 to 1997 and then in 2002, before going on hiatus.
From 2003 to 2007, Stevenson played in smaller bands until All played shows again in 2008.
From 2003 to 2007, Stevenson played in smaller bands until All played shows again in 2008.
In 2010, the Descendents reformed again.
He grew a brain tumor unknowingly around 2008, which remained for another two years before being removed.
In 2010, he had a successful surgery to remove it which helped him to gain his health back.
In 2016, Stevenson revealed he had open heart surgery.
